01:30.960 --> 01:32.540
So, Rich, I'm driving
along in my car,

01:32.540 --> 01:35.040
and all of a sudden it started
making these weird noises.

01:35.040 --> 01:36.050
(distant siren wailing)
What noises?

01:36.050 --> 01:38.050
K-pec, k-pec,
k-pec, then...

01:38.050 --> 01:40.020
(blowing raspberry)

01:40.020 --> 01:42.050
What a bod.

01:42.050 --> 01:44.550
Who cares about the body
if the engine doesn't work?

01:44.550 --> 01:47.060
It kept going k-pec,
k-pec, k-pec,

01:47.060 --> 01:48.560
I took it to the Fonz

01:48.560 --> 01:50.030
when it started going
k-pok, k-pok--

01:50.030 --> 01:53.060
K-wow, k-wow, k-wow.

01:54.060 --> 01:55.570
Hi.

01:55.570 --> 01:57.070
My name's
Ralph Malph.

01:57.070 --> 01:58.570
I start college
in the fall.

01:58.570 --> 02:00.370
(siren blaring)

02:02.070 --> 02:04.160
Air raid! Air raid!

02:04.660 --> 02:06.160
Don't panic,
this is just a drill.

02:06.660 --> 02:07.580
Everybody head for
the basement.

02:07.910 --> 02:11.000
Al, Al, a fire engine
went by, that's all.

02:11.500 --> 02:13.000
Oh, pshaw,

02:13.000 --> 02:15.470
I never get to wear
the helmet.

02:15.800 --> 02:18.810
We're starting our
own fire right here.

02:19.140 --> 02:21.720
You're doing real good,
Gina.

02:21.720 --> 02:23.230
Hey, come here,
Ralph.

02:23.230 --> 02:24.730
What are you doing?

02:24.730 --> 02:25.730
I was right in the middle
of getting...

02:25.730 --> 02:27.730
You were right in the middle
of getting nothing.

02:27.730 --> 02:30.070
She's helping me out--
that happens to be my niece.

02:30.320 --> 02:32.850
Didn't you see
the resemblance?

02:34.740 --> 02:36.320
No.
No.

02:36.320 --> 02:39.080
Well, she's not
wearing a hat.

02:39.490 --> 02:41.080
Darling, you better
get down from there.

02:41.080 --> 02:42.580
You'll get hurt.
Come on.

02:42.580 --> 02:43.580
Aren't you cold?

02:43.580 --> 02:45.580
There's such a draft, here,
put this sweater on.

02:45.580 --> 02:47.080
It's too cold.

02:47.080 --> 02:49.090
(girls screaming)

02:49.090 --> 02:51.090
Oh, oh...

02:51.090 --> 02:52.090
Oh, it was awful.

02:52.090 --> 02:54.090
It was terrible.

03:00.100 --> 03:02.930
Oh, boy, I need some water.

03:03.220 --> 03:05.050
Fonz, was-was your
garage on fire?

03:05.270 --> 03:06.350
I'll tell you something,

03:06.350 --> 03:07.850
it was horrible...

03:07.850 --> 03:09.360
maybe oily rags...

03:09.360 --> 03:11.360
flames... swoosh!

03:11.360 --> 03:13.360
It was just terrible!

03:13.360 --> 03:16.200
Who's the new chick
with the hammer?

03:16.480 --> 03:19.070
Fonz, Fonz, listen,
you gotta sit down.

03:19.570 --> 03:21.570
Sit down and
take it easy.

03:21.570 --> 03:23.820
All right, now-now,
tell us what happened.

03:24.040 --> 03:26.620
I was in my office,
taking a nap, you know?

03:27.120 --> 03:28.630
And I was just--
this beautiful dream.

03:29.130 --> 03:30.630
I was on this
tropical island

03:31.130 --> 03:32.630
with two beautiful
chicks.

03:33.130 --> 03:34.130
Only two, Fonz?
Well, it was a--

03:34.580 --> 03:36.130
it was a short nap,
Malph.
Oh.

03:36.630 --> 03:38.130
But I'm telling you
something,

03:38.130 --> 03:40.140
if that guy wasn't there
that dragged me out,

03:40.140 --> 03:41.550
it would have been
curtains for the Fonz.

03:41.890 --> 03:42.840
Well, who? Who did it?

03:43.140 --> 03:45.230
I don't know, these two hands
came through the smoke,

03:45.230 --> 03:47.230
pulled me out,
that's all I know, huh?

03:47.230 --> 03:48.600
Pulled me out
of the garage.

03:48.900 --> 03:50.400
Okay, go on, Fonz.

03:50.730 --> 03:52.320
The next thing I know,

03:52.320 --> 03:55.320
I am lying flat on my back
on the sidewalk.

03:55.770 --> 03:58.320
And then some fireman wants
to give me a kiss.

04:00.240 --> 04:01.820
Oh, no.

04:02.330 --> 04:05.080
No, see, he was giving you
mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

04:06.360 --> 04:08.870
I knew that.

04:09.370 --> 04:11.670
He just should have told me
before I dented his helmet.

04:11.870 --> 04:13.950
Well-well, tell me,

04:14.450 --> 04:16.370
did you ever figure out
who it was that saved you?

04:16.760 --> 04:17.339
No.

04:17.839 --> 04:18.839
Somewhere out there,

04:18.839 --> 04:20.839
there is a guy walking
around in a Jefferson jacket,

04:20.839 --> 04:23.300
who saved the Fonz

04:23.300 --> 04:25.850
from being a barbecued
chicken.

04:25.850 --> 04:27.350
And I want to tell you
something.

04:27.850 --> 04:28.850
I want to tell you
something.

04:28.850 --> 04:30.850
Any favor he wants,
he gets.

04:31.270 --> 04:32.860
CROWD:
Wow!

04:33.270 --> 04:34.860
You need some
more water?
Oh, yeah.

04:34.860 --> 04:36.360
All right, more water,
more water,

04:36.360 --> 04:38.360
the man needs more water!

04:42.120 --> 04:44.120
Hey, Pots,

04:44.120 --> 04:46.120
what, did your father
make you clean the
chimney again?

04:46.120 --> 04:47.620
It was terrible!

04:47.620 --> 04:48.620
Wait a minute.

04:49.120 --> 04:50.120
Your were in
the fire?
Yeah.

04:50.120 --> 04:51.960
Here, have some
water.
Thanks.

04:52.210 --> 04:53.790
He's got a Jefferson jacket.

04:54.290 --> 04:55.300
Potsie saved you.

04:55.660 --> 04:58.250
Nah.

05:00.750 --> 05:02.250
It was incredible.

05:02.750 --> 05:03.750
That's Fonzie's
water.

05:05.250 --> 05:07.260
I was passing by the garage
when I smelled smoke.

05:07.260 --> 05:08.760
Then I heard screams.

05:08.760 --> 05:09.760
Aaayyh, aaayyh, aaayyh,
aaayyh, aaayyh, aaayyh.

05:10.260 --> 05:11.230
Oh, maybe not screams.

05:18.740 --> 05:20.740
Anyway, I ran inside,

05:20.740 --> 05:22.610
and I dragged
the Fonz out.

05:22.860 --> 05:24.440
Potsie,
you're a hero!

05:24.440 --> 05:25.940
(cheering and laughter)
Yeah?

05:26.440 --> 05:27.440
All right,
all right, ho!

05:27.440 --> 05:29.450
Just step back, girls,
step back.

