05:40.670 --> 05:41.670
Oh, Fonz.

05:42.180 --> 05:43.680
I'm the Italian;
I'll do the hugging.

05:45.180 --> 05:46.680
Unbelievable, Potsie,

05:47.180 --> 05:48.680
you did good.

05:49.180 --> 05:51.180
Any favor you want,
you got.

05:51.180 --> 05:53.050
(crowd murmuring)

05:53.350 --> 05:56.440
Now go wash up-- you look
like Smokey the Bear.

05:56.440 --> 05:58.220
Thanks, Fonz.
Yeah.

05:58.470 --> 06:00.360
Give him some air,
give him some air, come on.

06:00.560 --> 06:01.640
I'll tell you something,

06:02.150 --> 06:04.480
if it wasn't for him,
I'd look like Ralph's car.

06:04.780 --> 06:06.370
(chuckles)

06:09.370 --> 06:11.370
You mean he left my car
in the garage?

06:11.370 --> 06:12.370
He went off
without it?

06:12.870 --> 06:13.870
Well, maybe he didn't
have time.

06:13.870 --> 06:15.240
He had time
to pull him out!

06:15.490 --> 06:16.410
Aaayyh.

06:16.660 --> 06:17.740
Sorry, Fonz.

06:17.740 --> 06:19.250
Oh, no, my car!

06:19.660 --> 06:21.250
(piano playing)

06:21.750 --> 06:24.750
HOWARD:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">It's time to go to the Open
House at school, Marion{\r}.</font></font></i>

06:24.750 --> 06:26.720
MARION:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">We're just about through
with Vickie's piano lesson{\r}.</font></font></i>

06:27.090 --> 06:28.670
Can I be finished now?

06:29.170 --> 06:31.090
Yes, Vickie, you
can be finished.

06:31.420 --> 06:33.510
Joanie, dear, will you get
Vickie's coat?

06:35.510 --> 06:37.510
There you go, dear.

06:37.510 --> 06:39.020
Howard...
Mmm?

06:39.020 --> 06:41.520
Remember when the children
were small?

06:41.520 --> 06:42.350
Yeah.

06:42.600 --> 06:44.690
Oh, I wish that
we had a little one

06:44.690 --> 06:47.070
around here sometimes.

06:50.440 --> 06:52.030
Well, we got ten
minutes, Marion.

06:56.530 --> 06:59.370
Howard, just put
your coat on.

06:59.620 --> 07:01.700
Oh, Dad, has Potsie
showed up here yet?

07:01.700 --> 07:03.210
Why would Potsie
come over here?

07:03.710 --> 07:04.710
We've already
had dinner.

07:05.210 --> 07:06.710
No, no, it's not
for dinner.

07:07.210 --> 07:08.710
See, uh,

07:08.710 --> 07:10.710
Fonzie feels that since
Potsie saved his life

07:10.710 --> 07:12.220
that he owes him a favor.

07:12.220 --> 07:13.720
Yeah, it's called
the Fonzarelli code.

07:13.720 --> 07:15.720
A man saves your life,

07:15.720 --> 07:18.720
any favor he asks,
you gotta answer it.

07:18.720 --> 07:20.720
You know?
I mean like in-in Sicily?

07:20.720 --> 07:23.560
Uncle Vito, he had his life
saved by a midget.

07:23.780 --> 07:25.360
A midget?
FONZIE:
Yeah.

07:25.360 --> 07:27.360
What did he ask for?

07:27.360 --> 07:28.650
Height!

07:29.900 --> 07:31.400
Well, in a way,
you know, in a way.

07:31.900 --> 07:33.400
Every time there was
a parade in town,

07:33.400 --> 07:34.400
Uncle Vito had
to take that midget,

07:34.400 --> 07:35.910
put him on his shoulders
so he could see.

07:36.410 --> 07:37.410
That's right,

07:37.410 --> 07:39.790
I-I was told it was
a very moving experience.

07:40.040 --> 07:41.630
You know, speaking
of moving,

07:41.630 --> 07:43.410
Ginny Picalow's project is
waiting.

07:43.630 --> 07:45.210
Yes, dear,

07:45.210 --> 07:47.630
we will make it to the
Open House on time.

07:47.970 --> 07:49.550
What's your project,
Joanie?

07:50.000 --> 07:51.050
Oh, I wrote a
composition,

07:51.470 --> 07:53.890
"My Parents are Still Frisky."

07:56.260 --> 07:57.760
Howard,

07:58.260 --> 07:59.760
she-she wouldn't.

08:00.260 --> 08:01.760
Well, who knows,
Marion?

08:01.760 --> 08:03.270
What will we do
if she reads it

08:03.270 --> 08:05.770
in front of the whole
auditorium?

08:05.770 --> 08:07.770
We'll move.
Good.

08:07.770 --> 08:09.160
(doorbell rings)

08:09.520 --> 08:10.610
Oh, I bet that's
Potsie.

08:11.110 --> 08:12.830
What do you think he's gonna ask
for, Fonz?
Well,

08:13.080 --> 08:15.410
what do you think goes with his
Huckleberry Hound lunch box?

08:17.660 --> 08:18.700
Hey, Rich.
Oh, come on in,
guys.

08:18.700 --> 08:20.200
Yeah.
Thanks, Richie.

08:20.200 --> 08:21.200
Hey, Fonz.
Hey.
Hi, Fonz.

08:21.200 --> 08:22.200
What are you
doing here?

08:22.200 --> 08:24.200
My car's all burned up,
remember?

08:24.200 --> 08:26.010
Potsie's giving me
a ride home.

08:26.210 --> 08:27.290
Yeah, it's hard,

08:27.290 --> 08:28.760
he keeps getting his feet stuck
in the spokes.

08:29.180 --> 08:31.260
Well, if you didn't have
your sister's bike,

08:31.760 --> 08:33.100
I wouldn't have to ride
on the handlebars.

08:33.299 --> 08:34.380
Oh, you're lucky
you got a ride at all.

08:34.799 --> 08:36.380
All right, all right, here,
time out here, time out,

08:36.380 --> 08:37.880
we're not here to bicker
about bicycles.

08:37.880 --> 08:39.890
You had a whole day
to think about it,

08:39.890 --> 08:41.220
now what do you want, Potsie?

08:41.470 --> 08:42.559
All right, now anything
you want, Potsie,

08:42.559 --> 08:44.560
anything at all, Fonzie
will give it to you,

08:44.560 --> 08:46.360
you just tell him
what you want.
Uh, Cunningham?

08:46.560 --> 08:47.640
Let us not push the kid.

08:47.640 --> 08:49.650
Oh.
What do you want now?

08:49.650 --> 08:50.950
A new thermos
for your lunch box?

08:51.150 --> 08:53.230
Or, uh, uh, uh,

08:53.230 --> 08:54.730
a new-- a new bell
for your bike?

08:55.230 --> 08:56.700
A date with the Aloha
Pussycats?

08:57.240 --> 08:58.240
Can be arranged.
Take 'em!

08:58.240 --> 08:59.740
Take the Pussycats!

08:59.740 --> 09:00.740
No.

09:01.240 --> 09:02.240
No, I don't think
I want that.

09:02.240 --> 09:04.240
But, can I sit down
for a minute, Fonz?

09:04.240 --> 09:05.750
Yeah, sure.
Aw, thanks.

09:05.750 --> 09:06.580
Uh...

09:06.880 --> 09:08.970
I've given thought

09:09.470 --> 09:10.970
to different
things, Fonz.

09:10.970 --> 09:13.300
And, uh, well, I picked
something that means
a lot to me.

09:13.590 --> 09:15.170
Shoot.

09:15.170 --> 09:16.060
Yeah.

09:17.420 --> 09:19.260
I want to pal around
with you, Fonz.

09:28.070 --> 09:30.020
You want to, uh,
pal around?

09:30.020 --> 09:32.070
Yeah.
With me?

09:32.440 --> 09:34.020
Yeah.

09:34.520 --> 09:36.030
You and I together,
all the time.

09:36.530 --> 09:38.030
Just like this...

09:38.530 --> 09:40.450
pal.

09:40.910 --> 09:42.500
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

09:42.500 --> 09:43.780
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

09:43.950 --> 09:46.540
♪ La, la, la, la... ♪

09:53.840 --> 09:54.930
Pals, huh?

09:54.930 --> 09:55.930
Potsie-- pals.

09:55.930 --> 09:56.930
Look, we are pals.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.430
Don't you want something
more exciting?

09:58.430 --> 09:59.930
How about a, uh,
a piano!

10:00.430 --> 10:01.430
Oh, uh,

10:01.430 --> 10:02.440
no, Fonz.

10:02.440 --> 10:03.890
I want to be
your special pal.

10:04.270 --> 10:05.720
Why?

10:07.060 --> 10:09.060
Well, I never had a sp--

10:09.560 --> 10:11.060
well, kids do things
with their fathers, right?

10:11.560 --> 10:13.400
Ralph and his dad go fishing
together.

10:13.700 --> 10:15.280
Oh yeah, he puts
worms in my shoes

10:15.280 --> 10:16.780
and I put minnows
down his back.

10:16.780 --> 10:17.730
It's great,
he loves it.

10:18.120 --> 10:19.150
Yeah!

10:19.570 --> 10:21.150
I know what I'm gonna do,

10:21.150 --> 10:22.660
I'm gonna get you
a fishing pole

10:22.660 --> 10:23.990
and a can of
worms, huh?

10:24.210 --> 10:25.790
Aw, Rich and his dad
are so close

10:25.790 --> 10:27.580
he even told him
about sex.

10:27.830 --> 10:30.410
Yeah, but he got most
of it wrong, anyway.

10:33.050 --> 10:35.550
Look, uh, Potsie,
look, uh,

10:35.550 --> 10:37.550
you know being pals, that's
a-- that's a cute idea...

10:37.550 --> 10:38.550
I knew you'd like it,
Fonz!

10:38.550 --> 10:40.060
I'll give you
my phone number.

10:40.060 --> 10:42.560
We'll do everything
I never got to do
with my father.

10:42.560 --> 10:44.390
I think I just adopted Potsie.

10:45.850 --> 10:47.350
Yeah, well,
I-I don't think

10:47.350 --> 10:49.350
he means he wants to spend
every minute with you.

10:49.350 --> 10:52.230
Oh, no, Fonz, he only
means about three or
four times a week,

10:52.570 --> 10:54.150
right, Pots?
Oh, yeah.

10:54.150 --> 10:56.160
Here, Fonz, you need
some time to yourself.

10:56.160 --> 10:57.160
Aaayyh.

10:57.160 --> 10:59.160
Whoa.

11:01.160 --> 11:03.160
Oh, I got a great idea
for Tuesday night.

11:03.160 --> 11:04.660
Oh, yeah?

11:04.660 --> 11:06.170
Where are the pals going?
The circus?

11:06.670 --> 11:09.170
(humming circus theme)

11:09.170 --> 11:12.120
How would you like to
be a fist swallower?

11:14.340 --> 11:16.930
Nah, Ralph, the circus
isn't until Thursday.

11:17.430 --> 11:18.930
Tuesday, we can go
to the bumper cars.

11:18.930 --> 11:20.710
Bumper cars!
Yeah.

11:22.010 --> 11:23.800
Sounds like big
fun, Fonz.

11:23.970 --> 11:25.550
Oh, hey, Fonz,
I know it sounds silly,

11:26.050 --> 11:26.890
but I never did it.

11:27.190 --> 11:28.770
All right, all right,
we'll do it.

11:28.770 --> 11:30.270
We'll do it.
Oh, great!

11:30.270 --> 11:31.270
Ooh, hey!

11:31.270 --> 11:32.730
Next week, we can go
roller-skating.

11:33.110 --> 11:34.190
Oh, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

11:34.190 --> 11:36.200
Forget it,
I don't skate.

11:36.200 --> 11:37.560
I'll teach you.

11:37.860 --> 11:38.900
Hey, don't--

11:38.900 --> 11:39.950
Come on, don't you
want a date

11:40.450 --> 11:42.230
with the Aloha
Pussycats?

11:42.490 --> 11:43.570
Oh, yeah.

11:44.070 --> 11:45.570
Bring them along, too.

11:46.070 --> 11:47.070
I'll teach them.

11:47.070 --> 11:49.040
See you, buddies.

11:49.040 --> 11:51.080
So long, pal.

11:57.050 --> 11:59.920
There is nothing
he can teach them.

12:00.250 --> 12:02.090
Hey, Fonz, are you
afraid to skate?

12:02.300 --> 12:03.390
Afraid?

12:03.390 --> 12:05.390
If the man upstairs
wanted us to skate,

12:05.390 --> 12:07.390
we would be born with little
wheels on our feet.

12:13.600 --> 12:15.680
♪ ♪

12:22.690 --> 12:24.190
(whistle blows)

12:24.190 --> 12:27.700
MALE ANNOUNCER:
All right, everybody down
to the north end of the rink

12:27.700 --> 12:29.200
for the three-legged skate race.

12:29.200 --> 12:31.200
(excited murmuring)

12:35.200 --> 12:36.710
Hey, wait a minute.

12:36.710 --> 12:37.710
What happened
to Fonzie?

12:38.210 --> 12:40.710
He's right
behind us.

12:40.710 --> 12:42.210
Come on.

12:42.210 --> 12:44.180
Isabell Polinka
just went by.

12:44.180 --> 12:46.720
It looks like she
split her seam.

12:46.720 --> 12:48.180
Whip!
Double whip!

12:48.600 --> 12:50.190
I'll wait for Fonz.

13:07.570 --> 13:09.410
Hey, come on, Fonz.

13:09.870 --> 13:10.820
Fonz, it's really
terrific.

13:10.820 --> 13:12.320
Now just come on
down here.

13:16.210 --> 13:17.800
Come on.

13:25.810 --> 13:27.810
Excellent, Fonz, ex...

13:27.810 --> 13:29.310
Whoa, Fonz...

13:36.150 --> 13:38.100
Fonz, I can't believe you
didn't skate as a child.

13:38.100 --> 13:40.650
I was never a child.

13:40.650 --> 13:43.160
Look, all those children
are skating.

13:43.160 --> 13:44.610
Let's do something
grown-ups do.

13:44.610 --> 13:45.660
No, wait, Fonz, watch.

13:45.660 --> 13:46.660
Watch me,
it's real easy.

13:46.660 --> 13:50.660
Just watch me,
relax and glide.

13:50.660 --> 13:51.700
See?
Great.

13:51.700 --> 13:53.200
Nothing to it.

13:53.200 --> 13:56.200
Come on, all the
cute chicks are out there.

13:56.200 --> 13:58.200
Somehow, I got a feeling
they're gonna come around.

13:58.200 --> 14:00.210
I'm gonna wait for
them right here.

14:00.210 --> 14:01.670
Yeah, well,
I'll tell you,

14:01.670 --> 14:03.710
I'm gonna go scout around,
but don't worry,

14:03.710 --> 14:06.210
I'm gonna get you
set up for tonight, pal.

14:12.220 --> 14:13.550
Hey, Fonz.

14:14.890 --> 14:15.800
Where's Richie?

14:16.140 --> 14:17.720
Oh, he's skating
behind Isabell Polinka.

14:17.720 --> 14:20.230
He's waiting
for her seam to go.

14:20.730 --> 14:21.230
POTSIE:
Hey, Fonz, look!

14:21.640 --> 14:23.730
Backwards... hey.

14:23.730 --> 14:24.700
Hey.

14:25.060 --> 14:26.150
(whistle blowing)

14:26.150 --> 14:29.150
Hey, Fonz, Potsie showed us
your circus pictures.

14:29.150 --> 14:30.070
(laughing)

14:31.990 --> 14:34.490
Malph, the man
saved my life.

14:34.910 --> 14:35.990
Oh, but you
looked so cute

14:35.990 --> 14:37.830
with your little
clown's hat and balloon.

14:40.160 --> 14:41.660
Just cool it!

14:41.660 --> 14:42.670
Sorry, Fonz, sorry.

14:42.670 --> 14:44.670
All right, get me up.

14:44.670 --> 14:45.670
Anybody see?

14:45.670 --> 14:46.590
No, no.

14:48.500 --> 14:50.010
Fonz, I missed you
yesterday.

14:50.010 --> 14:50.920
Where were you?

14:51.310 --> 14:53.890
Well, I went to Potsie's
family reunion.

14:53.890 --> 14:57.900
Wall-to-wall Potsies.

14:58.310 --> 14:59.850
POTSIE:
Fonz, Fonz, guess what?

14:59.850 --> 15:02.400
You'll never be...

15:02.900 --> 15:04.150
Sorry.

15:04.350 --> 15:05.440
Sorry, pal,
I didn't...

15:05.440 --> 15:06.440
I didn't mean it.

15:06.440 --> 15:07.940
Pal.

15:07.940 --> 15:09.940
It's just... it's just
that there's a bunch

15:10.440 --> 15:11.910
of cute chicks on the
other side of the rink.

15:12.280 --> 15:13.860
Oh, yeah? Come on Pots,
let's go trip

15:14.280 --> 15:15.360
some of those girls.

15:15.360 --> 15:16.370
I better go.

15:16.370 --> 15:17.700
Never had so much
fun, huh, Fonz?

15:17.920 --> 15:19.500
Fun, lot of fun.

15:19.500 --> 15:21.040
(whistle blowing)

15:21.540 --> 15:24.870
Kathy, Scott,
look at this.

15:25.170 --> 15:26.680
Hey, mister,
what's the matter?

15:29.600 --> 15:32.100
First of all, I ain't a mister,
and second of all,

15:32.100 --> 15:34.430
why don't you go off and play?

15:34.630 --> 15:35.720
ALL:
Why?

15:35.720 --> 15:37.720
He wants us
to get out of here

15:37.720 --> 15:38.720
'cause he doesn't know
how to skate.

15:40.560 --> 15:42.140
He doesn't know
how to skate?

15:42.140 --> 15:44.110
ALL:
Na, na, na-na, na.

15:49.950 --> 15:52.450
(mocking):
Na, na, na-na, na.

15:52.450 --> 15:56.960
Little kids can do this, Potsie
can do this, I can do this.

15:57.370 --> 15:59.460
(rattling)

16:17.930 --> 16:19.510
Hey.

16:33.190 --> 16:36.000
Oh, be careful!

16:36.160 --> 16:39.110
Say, I could give you
some lessons.

16:39.420 --> 16:40.500
Yeah, you take
off those skates,

16:40.500 --> 16:42.280
I'll give <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">you
some lessons{\r}.</font></font></i>

16:43.620 --> 16:44.620
Gee, I think
your lessons

16:45.120 --> 16:46.370
might be a
little bit more fun.

16:46.590 --> 16:48.170
Yeah, <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">correcto{\r}.</font></font></i>

16:48.170 --> 16:50.210
POTSIE:
Fonz, Fonz, I
saw you fall.

16:50.710 --> 16:51.710
Gosh... oh,
excuse me, ma'am.

16:52.210 --> 16:53.710
Here, out of the way,
I'll help my pal.

16:53.710 --> 16:54.710
I'll... I'll help him up.

16:54.710 --> 16:55.710
All right.

16:56.220 --> 16:57.220
Come on.

16:57.220 --> 16:59.220
Are you crazy?

16:59.220 --> 17:00.220
Oh, my gosh.

17:00.220 --> 17:01.720
Oh, here, Fonz, let me...
here, come on.

17:01.720 --> 17:03.720
I promise I'll go
get her back for you.

17:03.720 --> 17:05.220
Just stand right here,
I'll go get her.

17:05.220 --> 17:06.730
Don't move, Fonz.

17:16.069 --> 17:18.569
(skates rolling)

17:29.420 --> 17:30.920
I'm still standing.

17:30.920 --> 17:33.720
I'm getting good at this.

17:33.920 --> 17:35.470
All right.

17:37.510 --> 17:39.310
Hey, get over here.

17:41.090 --> 17:43.600
Hey, uh, Potsie,
take it easy.

17:43.980 --> 17:45.900
Turn around.

17:46.150 --> 17:48.730
Elm Street, 4222,
get out of here.

17:54.190 --> 17:59.700
♪ Pretend you're happy
when you're blue ♪

18:00.110 --> 18:02.700
♪ It isn't very hard to do ♪
Psst.

18:02.700 --> 18:04.700
RALPH:
All right,
Fonz, you're...

18:04.700 --> 18:07.700
I fixed your car,
it's in the garage, huh?

18:07.700 --> 18:09.710
All right, Fonz!

18:09.710 --> 18:12.460
He fixed my car,
my trusty car.

18:12.670 --> 18:15.210
Inspiration Point,
here I come.

18:21.050 --> 18:22.890
(snaps fingers)

18:23.190 --> 18:24.640
Where's Potsie?

18:24.890 --> 18:26.310
I don't know,
I think he split,

18:26.610 --> 18:27.690
but I can probably
find him for you

18:28.190 --> 18:29.190
if you
want me to, Fonz.

18:29.190 --> 18:30.690
Oh, yeah, you don't
want me to find him.

18:30.690 --> 18:33.200
All right, in
my office.

18:33.200 --> 18:34.700
Feel like playing
some basketball?

18:34.700 --> 18:35.700
No.

18:40.450 --> 18:42.960
Cunningham, I'm telling you,
it is making me crazy.

18:42.960 --> 18:44.460
I got to stop this.

18:44.460 --> 18:46.330
I got to find some way
to stop this.

18:46.580 --> 18:47.490
Well, is it Potsie?

18:47.790 --> 18:48.880
No, no, no, it's not Potsie.

18:48.880 --> 18:51.380
I-I'm having trouble learning
how to crochet.

18:51.800 --> 18:54.380
(chuckling):
Yeah, crochet.

18:54.380 --> 18:55.830
Will you give me
that ball.

18:55.830 --> 18:57.390
Of course, it's Potsie.

18:57.390 --> 18:58.390
Everywhere I go,

18:58.390 --> 19:00.390
everywhere I turn,
he is there.

19:00.390 --> 19:03.390
It's like having gum
on your shoe.

19:03.390 --> 19:04.890
Well, it can't
be that bad.

19:04.890 --> 19:06.310
Potsie's a
pretty nice guy.

19:06.650 --> 19:07.730
Yeah, so is Pinky Lee,

19:07.730 --> 19:10.230
but I don't go
roller-skating with him.

19:10.650 --> 19:14.150
Fonz, why don't you just
break the Fonzarelli Code?

19:14.490 --> 19:16.520
Yeah, it's not
just the code, Red.

19:16.520 --> 19:18.070
It's not just the code.

19:18.570 --> 19:21.080
You see, I mean, I feel
this way about anybody.

19:21.080 --> 19:23.080
You know, I mean,
I like him.

19:23.080 --> 19:25.950
It's just the Fonz
needs his room.

19:26.280 --> 19:28.330
Why don't you just tell him
to pick something else?

19:28.330 --> 19:30.250
Maybe he'll choose
the Aloha Pussycats.

19:30.590 --> 19:32.540
Yeah, and maybe he'll
choose to be my roomie.

19:33.960 --> 19:36.930
I got to face it, I got to help
him relive his childhood.

19:36.930 --> 19:40.460
It's just a wonderful life
of circuses and bumper cars.

19:43.470 --> 19:44.970
Well, it's not too bad, Fonz.

19:44.970 --> 19:46.770
The rodeo is coming
to town next week.

19:48.020 --> 19:49.100
Roy Rogers!

19:49.100 --> 19:50.610
Trigger does tricks.

19:50.610 --> 19:51.440
He knows how to count.

19:55.780 --> 19:57.280
Cunningham...

19:57.280 --> 19:59.780
Right, sorry, Fonz.

19:59.780 --> 20:01.780
I heard Trigger also
knows how to multiply.

20:01.780 --> 20:03.240
Get out of here!

20:06.740 --> 20:09.580
I ask him for advice...
he counts like a horse.

20:27.480 --> 20:28.260
You...?

20:28.510 --> 20:29.510
You... wait.

20:32.100 --> 20:34.180
I-I just came
to get the...

20:46.280 --> 20:47.610
Hey, Fonz.

20:49.000 --> 20:51.000
My pal's here,
I got... split.

20:52.500 --> 20:54.290
How you doing, Pots?
Where you been?

20:54.500 --> 20:56.460
Oh, you know, Fonz,
I've been around.

20:56.790 --> 20:57.870
Yeah, what festivities
you got planned

20:58.370 --> 21:00.180
for me tonight,
a little skeet ball?

21:00.380 --> 21:01.960
Oh, no, nothing like that.

21:01.960 --> 21:03.460
No, but...

21:03.460 --> 21:05.460
can I sit down and talk
to you for a second?

21:05.850 --> 21:06.770
Sit down, shoot.

21:07.020 --> 21:08.100
Thanks.

21:08.100 --> 21:11.100
Uh...

21:11.100 --> 21:13.610
I just want you
to know that, uh,

21:13.610 --> 21:15.610
I really appreciate you
letting me hang around.

21:15.610 --> 21:18.110
I mean, I never never
had a big brother

21:18.110 --> 21:18.980
or anything like that.

21:19.310 --> 21:20.810
Hey, Pots...
It's really...

21:20.810 --> 21:21.810
you saved my life.

21:22.200 --> 21:25.280
Yeah, I saved your life.

21:25.280 --> 21:28.290
Oh, hey, I-I really
had a great time at the circus.

21:28.790 --> 21:30.290
I framed that picture of you
with the balloon.

21:30.710 --> 21:32.290
Yeah, hey, uh, do me
a favor on that one, will you?

21:32.290 --> 21:33.290
Hang that one in the closet.

21:34.790 --> 21:37.300
I understand, sure.

21:37.300 --> 21:42.300
I mean... we really had
a lot of fun together.

21:42.800 --> 21:46.310
That's why it's really hard
to tell you that, uh...

21:46.310 --> 21:48.670
we just can't hang around
together anymore.

21:51.890 --> 21:52.890
We can't?

21:53.310 --> 21:55.400
No, uh...

21:55.900 --> 21:58.730
you see, Fonz, I need my room.

21:58.980 --> 22:03.570
Hey, now, that's funny,
because I just, uh...

22:03.570 --> 22:04.940
yeah, I was just saying that.

22:05.240 --> 22:06.690
Yeah, so you know what I mean.

22:06.990 --> 22:07.940
I sure do.

22:08.240 --> 22:10.200
And we can still
be friends, right?

22:10.500 --> 22:12.360
I mean...

22:12.610 --> 22:15.620
I figure... you'd do the same
for me in a fire.

22:16.000 --> 22:17.870
Hey, you got it, Pots.

22:18.120 --> 22:20.210
I got it.

22:20.210 --> 22:22.710
So, Fonz, uh...

22:25.210 --> 22:26.510
you don't owe me
anything anymore.

22:31.050 --> 22:33.140
Hey, my date's here.

22:51.400 --> 22:52.290
Pots?

22:53.910 --> 22:55.320
You're all right.

22:55.570 --> 22:57.080
Thanks, Rich.

22:57.380 --> 23:00.960
I was supposed to have a date
with Isabell Polinka tonight,

23:00.960 --> 23:02.960
but she's home sewing her seam.

23:06.800 --> 23:08.300
Would you like going down
to the gym

23:08.300 --> 23:09.810
and playing some basketball?

23:09.810 --> 23:11.310
I'm trying to work
on my left hand dribble.

23:11.720 --> 23:14.260
(muttering):
No, that's okay.

23:14.640 --> 23:16.730
I'll introduce you
to some of my friends.

23:19.230 --> 23:20.730
Hey, Fonz.

23:21.230 --> 23:23.070
Looks like you're gonna
have a hot time tonight.

23:23.270 --> 23:24.850
What are you talking about, me?

23:24.850 --> 23:27.360
Me and Pots are going
to have a hot time tonight,

23:27.360 --> 23:29.240
if you got one more "pal night"
left inside you.

23:32.110 --> 23:33.110
All right, Fonz!

23:33.110 --> 23:34.610
FONZIE:
All right.

23:34.610 --> 23:36.000
Oh... three for me
and three for you?

23:36.330 --> 23:37.330
Well, don't get excited,
you know?

23:37.670 --> 23:39.250
Oh.

23:41.750 --> 23:42.670
Four and two?

23:43.000 --> 23:43.920
Hey.

23:44.120 --> 23:45.670
Hey, Fonz, can I have
the one on the left?

23:46.090 --> 23:47.680
Yeah... my left.

23:47.680 --> 23:49.180
Right, right.

23:50.600 --> 23:52.010
FONZIE:
All right,

23:52.260 --> 23:54.770
let's go trip the light
fantastic.

23:55.050 --> 23:56.130
Okay.

23:56.130 --> 23:57.020
Whoa!

23:57.300 --> 24:00.390
♪ Aloha-ay ♪

24:00.390 --> 24:04.230
♪ Aloha-ay ♪

24:05.530 --> 24:07.030
Hey, Rich.

24:07.530 --> 24:08.860
Aloha.

24:19.710 --> 24:20.710
The ball.

24:21.210 --> 24:23.210
Oh, I know, I'm sorry.

24:23.210 --> 24:25.210
All those guys ever
think about is chicks.

24:25.210 --> 24:26.160
Yeah.

24:26.500 --> 24:28.470
There are other things,
you know, like sports.

24:28.800 --> 24:31.470
Cooking.
And school:
more important things.

24:33.840 --> 24:35.340
BOTH:
Nah.

24:37.340 --> 24:40.350
BOTH:
♪ Aloha-ay ♪

